// Regression: libFuzzer, 2026-04-18. `variants[` (9 bytes) drove ParseVariants
// into an allocation-bomb infinite loop — Consume() failures on the bracket
// token left `current` unchanged every iteration while still allocating a
// PipelineVariantDeclData per cycle. This represented 83% of the 226 hang
// artifacts in the 1-hour fuzz run.
//
// Fix: Parser::ProgressGuard RAII helper (bwsl_parser_soa.h) applied to all
// 23 recovery-prone parser loops. If a full iteration consumes no tokens,
// the destructor forces a single Advance() so the loop always makes progress.
// Expected: compiler exits cleanly with a parse error, not a hang.
variants[
